description.plain:
A1 x J1 is a duo consisting of North West London artist, Phinehas Waweru aka. A1orFundz, and Kent artist Joshua Somerkun aka. J1Mulla.

The two uprising talents gained widespread recognition after achieving a viral hit with their debut single “Latest Trends”, which started out as a viral snippet on the video-sharing social networking service “TikTok”, later being released on February 11th 2021.

Following the critical and commercial success of the single, including landing at Number 2 on the Official UK Singles Charts, the “Latest Trends” remix featuring popular Manchester rapper Aitch, was released a month later, on March 11th 2021.

description.plain:
“Latest Trends” serves as the debut single for 15-year old North West London (based in Coventry) artist, A1, and 17-year old Kent artist J1.

The single launched as a 15 second tease on the social media site Houseparty, which saw a massive influx of popularity following the COVID-19 Lockdown. The song officially found it’s way to video-sharing social media site TikTok where it starting soaring, with around 2000 videos creations a day with the snippet.

Social media eventually got the duo trending as they begged for the song to release – with the single officially dropping on the 4th of February, 2021.

Smoothly drifting along a suave guitar-based instrumental by ShoBeatz, the teenagers speak on their upbringing and explore their aspirations in wanting to make it with their music.

description.plain:
“Baby” is the second single released by teenage duo A1 x J1, and follows their critically acclaimed debut “Latest Trends” released in February 2021, and the Aitch assisted “Latest Trends” remix, released in March 2021.

The single was teased on 16th April 2021 on A1 x J1’s 100K Special video, a thank you video to the fans for getting them to 100K subscribers on YouTube, and is expected for release in May 2021.

songs.full_title: [A1 x J1] Plugged In Freestyle by A1 x J1
songs.title: [A1 x J1] Plugged In Freestyle

description.plain:
Teenage duo A1 x J1’s freestyle on Fumez The Engineer’s Plugged In series marks their first appearance following their viral smash-hit debut single “Latest Trends” – as well as two remixes from Manchester MC Aitch and New York rapper A Boogie wit da Hoodie.

A1 & J1 separate this freestyle within two parts. The teenagers go back-to-back as they explore their topics of love, heartbreak, their meteoric come up and their haters. A1 providing a lively and soothing ode through his infectious melodies as J1 sets the pace with his quality flow and expert wordplay.
